Class OutMessage

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.neebal.android.simplyreliable.message.Message
      • com.neebal.android.simplyreliable.message.OutMessage
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    DeleteMessage, GetMessage, HeadMessage, PayLoadMessage

    public abstract class OutMessage
extends Message
    An abstract representation of an outgoing message that needs to be sent to the server
    Since:
    1.0
    Author:
    Neebal Technologies
    See Also:
    GetMessage, PayLoadMessage, DeleteMessage, HeadMessage, Serialized Form

      • OutMessage

        public OutMessage(Resource resourcePath,
          SimplyReliableMsgIntf callback)
        Build an OutMessage instance using the Resource path and SimplyReliableMsgIntf callback.

        Note: By default this message instance will be asynchronous in nature.
        Parameters:
        resourcePath - the Resource path where the REST request needs to be sent to
        callback - the callback on which the methods will be called after getting the response/error response from the server
        Note: The callback is suppose to be a Serializable instance as it will be persisted in the underlying data store. Common mistake would be to create this callback as an inner type in say an Activity class. This would require the entire Activity instance to be Serializable (which is definitely not a good idea!). Create a separate class for this callback instance and see to it that the members are serializable

        public void setUpdateMsgComponentsIntf(UpdateMsgComponentsIntf updateMsgComponentsIntf)
        Sets the UpdateMsgComponentsIntf callback on this OutMessage instance.
        Parameters:
        updateMsgComponentsIntf - the instance of the callback that will run whenever all the dependencies associated with the OutMessage instance are fulfilled.

        Note: By setting the UpdateMsgComponentsIntf to this OutMessage instance, the API will mark all the msg components (url and body) as uninitialized.

      • checkStatus

        public void checkStatus()
                 throws ResourceNotFoundException,
                        InternalServerErrorException,
                        BadRequestException,
                        UserUnauthorizedException,
                        ForbiddenException,
                        InvalidResponseCodeException
        check the common set of status code that is returned by this http call. This implementation includes the handling of the common set of status codes for all the kinds of request (GET/POST/PUT/DELETE)
        Throws:
        ResourceNotFoundException - if the request was made for a resource that does not exist at the server side
        InternalServerErrorException - if there was some error at the server side
        BadRequestException - if data sent by the client caused an undesirable situation at the server side
        UserUnauthorizedException - if there was an unauthorized access to an authorized action
        ForbiddenException - if there was an access to an authorized action using wrong credentials
        InvalidResponseCodeException - if the response code returned by the server is not valid

      • executeServerCall

        public abstract void executeServerCall(HttpURLConnection connection)
                                throws IOException,
                                       CreateMultipartGetMsgFileException,
                                       GetMessageResponseFileStorageException
        The logic to make a request to the server and getting the response/headers back from the server should be done in this method. The implementation would depend upon the method type using which the request has to be made to the server.
        Note: Different subclass implementations can throw the below exceptions
        Parameters:
        connection - the HttpURLConnection connection object using which the call needs to be made to the server
        Throws:
        IOException - there was an i/o error at the time of connecting with the server or some error at the time of reading the input data
        CreateMultipartGetMsgFileException - if there is an error in creating the file for the artifact that was downloaded in the MultiPartGetMessage instance
        GetMessageResponseFileStorageException - if error at the time of saving the response from a GetMessage in the local file system

      • handleResponse

        public abstract boolean handleResponse()
                                throws GetMessageResponseFileStorageException,
                                       BadResponseException,
                                       InvalidResponseCodeException
        Handle the response returned for a particular OutMessage instance.
        Returns:
        a boolean value indicating whether the response was handled completely or no
        Throws:
        GetMessageResponseFileStorageException - if error at the time of saving the response from a GetMessage in the local file system
        BadResponseException - if invalid status code of response was returned from the server
        InvalidResponseCodeException - if the response code returned by the server for this message is invalid
